                <p>
                    <app loc="2"><lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ανο<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg><supplied reason="lost">Στέφ</supplied>ανο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg><note>or</note> <supplied reason="lost">Αἰγλ</supplied>άνο<supplied reason="lost">ρος</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible (voir commentaire).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable (see commentary).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile (vedi commento).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد (انظر التعليق على النقش)</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Two possible restorations are given in the apparatus for line 2. Depending on the case (nominative or genitive) of that line, the name Diogenes
               at line 1 would be at the nominative or genitive. In the present condition of the stone, this cannot be decided.</p>
